======================================================================
PART 1: S_n ORBITS = ISOMORPHISM CLASSES
======================================================================

n=3: 2 orbits (isomorphism classes)
  H= 1: 1 orbits, sizes=[6]
  H= 3: 1 orbits, sizes=[2]
  Burnside: Σ|Fix(σ)|/|S_n| = 12/6 = 2.0

n=4: 4 orbits (isomorphism classes)
  H= 1: 1 orbits, sizes=[24]
  H= 3: 2 orbits, sizes=[8, 8]
  H= 5: 1 orbits, sizes=[24]
  Burnside: Σ|Fix(σ)|/|S_n| = 96/24 = 4.0

n=5: 12 orbits (isomorphism classes)
  H= 1: 1 orbits, sizes=[120]
  H= 3: 3 orbits, sizes=[40, 40, 40]
  H= 5: 2 orbits, sizes=[120, 120]
  H= 9: 2 orbits, sizes=[120, 120]
  H=11: 1 orbits, sizes=[120]
  H=13: 1 orbits, sizes=[120]
  H=15: 2 orbits, sizes=[24, 40]
  Burnside: Σ|Fix(σ)|/|S_n| = 1440/120 = 12.0

======================================================================
PART 2: CHARACTERS OF S_n ON H-LEVEL SETS
======================================================================

n=4: Character table of S_n action on H-level sets:
    Cycle type |class|    H=1    H=3    H=5
  (1, 1, 1, 1)       1     24     16     24
     (2, 1, 1)       6      0      0      0
        (2, 2)       3      0      0      0
        (3, 1)       8      0      4      0
          (4,)       6      0      0      0

======================================================================
PART 3: IRREDUCIBLE DECOMPOSITION (n=4)
======================================================================

Decomposition of H-level S_4 representations:
  H=1: dim=24, 1·trivial + 1·sign + 3·standard + 3·sign_std + 2·V2 (dim check: 24)
  H=3: dim=16, 2·trivial + 2·sign + 2·standard + 2·sign_std (dim check: 16)
  H=5: dim=24, 1·trivial + 1·sign + 3·standard + 3·sign_std + 2·V2 (dim check: 24)

======================================================================
PART 4: CYCLE INDEX POLYNOMIAL
======================================================================

n=3: Cycle index on arc set:
     (1, 1, 1): 3 arc orbits [s1^3], 2^3 = 8 fixed
        (2, 1): 2 arc orbits [s1^1 s2^1], 2^2 = 4 fixed
          (3,): 1 arc orbits [s3^1], 2^1 = 2 fixed

n=4: Cycle index on arc set:
  (1, 1, 1, 1): 6 arc orbits [s1^6], 2^6 = 64 fixed
     (2, 1, 1): 4 arc orbits [s1^2 s2^2], 2^4 = 16 fixed
        (2, 2): 4 arc orbits [s1^2 s2^2], 2^4 = 16 fixed
        (3, 1): 2 arc orbits [s3^2], 2^2 = 4 fixed
          (4,): 2 arc orbits [s2^1 s4^1], 2^2 = 4 fixed

======================================================================
PART 5: FROBENIUS CHARACTER — H AS SYMMETRIC FUNCTION
======================================================================

n=4: Isomorphism classes with H and orbit size:
  T=  0: H=1, |orbit|=24, weight=1.0000
  T=  2: H=3, |orbit|=8, weight=0.3333
  T=  5: H=3, |orbit|=8, weight=0.3333
  T=  4: H=5, |orbit|=24, weight=1.0000

  Σ H * |orbit| = 192
  = n! * mean_H = 24 * 3.0

======================================================================
PART 6: TENSOR PRODUCTS IN REPRESENTATION RING
======================================================================

n=4: Tensor product structure of H-level representations:
  (Available from the irreducible decompositions above)
  V_h ⊗ V_h' can be computed from the character inner products
  V_1 ⊗ V_1: dim = 24 × 24 = 576
  V_1 ⊗ V_3: dim = 24 × 16 = 384
  V_1 ⊗ V_5: dim = 24 × 24 = 576
  V_3 ⊗ V_3: dim = 16 × 16 = 256
  V_3 ⊗ V_5: dim = 16 × 24 = 384
  V_5 ⊗ V_5: dim = 24 × 24 = 576

======================================================================
SYNTHESIS — REPRESENTATION THEORY
======================================================================

KEY FINDINGS:
1. S_n acts on tournaments by relabeling. H is invariant under this action.
2. Each H-level set carries an S_n representation that decomposes
   into irreducibles via the inner product formula.
3. At n=4: the decomposition into trivial, sign, standard, sign⊗standard,
   and V_2 representations reveals algebraic structure of H-level sets.
4. Cycle index on the arc set counts fixed tournaments per conjugacy class.
5. The Frobenius character encodes H as a symmetric function.
6. Tournament substitution gives an operad structure compatible with S_n.

